The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Tuesday, July 3, 2007

 Theatre festival

 Hutch Odeon 2007: Raybeshe Dance Theatre, at Nandan, 5.30pm; followed by Bhaowaiya and Bhatiyali performances, 6.30pm.

 On stage

 Poshu Khamar, an adaptation of George Orwells Animal Farm, by Pancham Vaidic, at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30pm.

 Sacrifice, based on Tagores Bisarjan, by Institute of Factual Theatre Arts, at Girish Mancha, 6.30pm.

 Talk

 Discourse on Sri Sri Ramakrishna Punthi, at Ramakrishna Math, Baranagar, 7.15pm.

 Music

 Lokbaddyer Oikotan, a concert using folk instruments of rural Bengal, organised by Bhromara, at Sisir Mancha, 6.30pm.

 Art watch

 Summer Show, works by various artists, at CIMA Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.

 Plurality, Unified Individualism, exhibition of works by various artists, at Birla Academy of Art and Culture, 4pm to 8pm.

 Vibrant Hues, exhibition of paintings by city artists, at Kanvas Art Gallery, 3pm to 7pm. 

 Tribute to Humanity, works by senior artists, at Angan Art Gallery, 4pm to 8pm. 

 Shadow on the Window, paintings by Arindam Chakraborty, at Chitrakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm. 

 Artoday, contemporary art from four cities, at Gallery Nakshatra, 11.30am to 7.30pm.

 Tapestry and Serigraphs by S.H.Raza, at Gallery K2, 3.30pm-7.30pm.

 Mystic Moods,works by Sukanta Das, at Masters Collection Art Gallery, 11am to 7pm.




